The paper deals with the problem of compressing massive tables, which is a topic that falls under the domain of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of combinatorial optimization techniques to improve compression rates suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the experimental results and use of machine learning algorithms suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
